data.title: Overcoming challenges in implementing the WHO Surgical Safety Checklist: lessons learnt from using a checklist training…
data.meta_description: The WHO Surgical Safety Checklist was launched in 2009, and appropriate use reduces mortality, surgical site infections and complications after surgery by up to 50%. Implementation across low-income and middle-income countries has been slow; published evidence is restricted to reports from a few single institutions, and significant challenges to successful implementation have been identified and presented.
